{"pageProps":{"problem":{"id":"t41-train-1","grade":"7","semester":"up","category":"方程","title":"针对训练1：新定义","difficulty":5,"tags":["方程","新定义"],"content":"\"*\" 对于任意有理数 $a$、$b$，规定一种新运算 $a * b = 3a - 2b$，例如 $5 * (-3) = 5 \\times 3 - (-3) \\times 2 = 21$。若 $(2x - 1) * x = -3 \\times (-3) = 21$，则 $x$ 的值为（  ）\n\nA. $-3$  B. $3$  C. $-1$  D. $1$","steps":[{"title":"解答","content":"根据新定义展开：$(2x - 1) * x = 3(2x - 1) - 2x$\n$= 6x - 3 - 2x = 4x - 3$\n令 $4x - 3 = 21$（根据题意）\n$4x = 24$，$x = 6$","formula":""}]},"id":"t41-train-1"},"__N_SSG":true}